# Anchorpipe Design System Rules

- Use Radix primitives + shadcn patterns; no ad-hoc components for primitives.
- Component tiers: primitives → base → composite; document usage and a11y notes.
- Tokens: colors, typography, spacing, motion; use tokens, not hard-coded values.
- Theming: support light/dark/high-contrast; avoid contrast regressions.
- Iconography: clarity/consistency/context; prefer curated set; avoid mixed stroke styles.
- Typography: follow defined scale; line-height/letter-spacing per spec; code uses monospace.
- Version components semantically; breaking changes require migration notes.
